  <div class="row">
    <div id="architecture" class="large-12 columns scrollto">
      <h1>Secure, self-hosted &amp; open source</h1>

      <p>umsatz was written with the assumption in mind that its users want to have complete control over where their accounting informations is stored.</p>

      <p>Since the original aim was to run umsatz on a raspberry pi we went to great length to optimize it for that scenario. The general architecture consists of multiple micro services all written in go, and a single page application displaying all the data.</p>

      <ul>
        <li>runs on any debian based *nix</li>
        <li>optimized for raspberry pi</li>
        <li>HTTP backends written in <a href="http://golang.org/" rel="nofollow">go</a>, SPA-frontend in JavaScript</li>
        <li>100% automatic deployment with <a href="http://www.ansible.com/" rel="nofollow">ansible</a></li>
        <li>support for i18n using <a href="http://i18next.com" rel="nofollow">i18next</a></li>
        <li>source code on <a href="https://github.com/umsatz" rel="nofollow">github.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p>All the code is open source - if you find it useful and want modifications feel free to send a pull request.</p>
    </div>
